# Memo conda

https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-set-up-jupyter-notebook-with-python-3-on-ubuntu-18-04

## Manage environments

Activate environment "base_env": 
	```source base_env/bin/activate``` or ```conda activate base_env```

Deactivate current environment: ```deactivate```


## Installing packages
Install <package> in <env> environment:
	```conda install -n <env> <package>```

To specify in which channel to search the package: 
	```conda install -n <env> --channel "channel" <package>```

Example: one may use conda-forge or [bioconda](https://anaconda.org/bioconda).

Bioconda: https://anaconda.org/bioconda